<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 12 at 5:45PM EDT  by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of east central Madison
and western Yancey Counties through 615 PM EDT...
At 545 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles northeast of Marshall, or near Mars Hill, moving east at 10
mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Mars Hill, Faust, Swiss and Wolf Ridge.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
